# Pronouns Reference Content

Cases in action - the words you'll use most frequently in Greek.

## Purpose

Show pronouns as the practical application of cases. High-frequency forms that demonstrate how cases work in daily speech.

## Key Insight

Pronouns are where you'll use cases most. Master these forms and cases click into place.

---

## Decision Guide (Hero Element)

<decision-guide name="pronoun-selection">
<question>Which "me/you" do I use?</question>

```
Position relative to the verb/noun?
├─ BEFORE verb → Object pronoun (accusative: με, σε, τον)
│   → "σε βλέπω" = I see you
│
├─ AFTER noun → Possessive pronoun (genitive: μου, σου, του)
│   → "το σπίτι μου" = my house
│
└─ AFTER preposition → Emphatic pronoun (εμένα, εσένα, αυτόν)
    → "για μένα" = for me
```
</decision-guide>

