## Pronoun Paradigms

### Accusative - Object Pronouns (Essential)

<paradigm name="accusative-pronouns" badge="Essential">
<rule>Go BEFORE the verb: σε βλέπω (you I-see) = I see you</rule>

| Person | Singular    | Plural        |
|--------|-------------|---------------|
| 1st    | με (me)     | μας (us)      |
| 2nd    | σε (you)    | σας (you pl.) |
| 3rd m  | τον (him)   | τους (them)   |
| 3rd f  | την (her)   | τις (them)    |
| 3rd n  | το (it)     | τα (them)     |

<examples>
- με βλέπεις; = do you see me?
- σε αγαπώ = I love you
- τον ξέρω = I know him
- μας περιμένουν = they're waiting for us
- σας ευχαριστώ = thank you (formal)
</examples>
</paradigm>

### Genitive - Possessive Pronouns (Essential)

<paradigm name="genitive-pronouns" badge="Essential">
<rule>Go AFTER the noun: το σπίτι μου (the house my) = my house</rule>
<note>Neuter uses same form as masculine (του)</note>

| Person | Singular     | Plural        |
|--------|--------------|---------------|
| 1st    | μου (my)     | μας (our)     |
| 2nd    | σου (your)   | σας (your pl.)|
| 3rd m  | του (his)    | τους (their)  |
| 3rd f  | της (her)    | τους (their)  |
| 3rd n  | του (its)    | τους (their)  |

<examples>
- το σπίτι μου = my house
- η μητέρα σου = your mother
- ο φίλος του = his friend
- το σπίτι μας = our house
- τα παιδιά τους = their children
</examples>
</paradigm>

### Nominative - Subject Pronouns

<paradigm name="nominative-pronouns">
<rule>Often dropped! Verb endings already show person.</rule>

| Person | Singular       | Plural         |
|--------|----------------|----------------|
| 1st    | εγώ (I)        | εμείς (we)     |
| 2nd    | εσύ (you)      | εσείς (you pl.)|
| 3rd m  | αυτός (he)     | αυτοί (they)   |
| 3rd f  | αυτή (she)     | αυτές (they)   |
| 3rd n  | αυτό (it)      | αυτά (they)    |

<examples>
- (εγώ) μιλάω = I speak (pronoun optional)
- αυτός μιλάει = HE speaks (for emphasis/clarity)
</examples>
</paradigm>

### Emphatic - After Prepositions

<paradigm name="emphatic-pronouns">
<rule>Use after prepositions (για, με, από, σε): για μένα = for me</rule>

| Person | Singular           | Plural             |
|--------|--------------------|--------------------|
| 1st    | εμένα/μένα (me)    | εμάς/μας (us)      |
| 2nd    | εσένα/σένα (you)   | εσάς/σας (you pl.) |
| 3rd m  | αυτόν (him)        | αυτούς (them)      |
| 3rd f  | αυτήν/αυτή (her)   | αυτές (them)       |
| 3rd n  | αυτό (it)          | αυτά (them)        |

<examples>
- για μένα = for me
- με σένα = with you
- για αυτόν = for him
- για αυτό = that's why / for this reason
</examples>
</paradigm>

